docs.lead_paragraph: The United States Court of Appeals in a two-to-one decision yesterday lifted an injunction that had barred the transfer of funds held by the First National City Bank of New York in its Montevideo, Uruguay, branch for the account of Omar, S.A., a Uruguayan holding company.
docs.abstract: US Appeals Ct, 2-1, vacates Dist Ct Nov '62 injunction on transfer of funds held by 1st Natl City Bank's Montevideo branch to Omar's acct because of Omar's alleged Fed tax delinquency; rules Fed Govt may not attach funds held in foreign branches of US banks
